OL,3,CModerator of the Presbyterian Church
OL,4,Cresigns over safeguarding failings
OL,6,FHe added: "Although not directly
OL,7,Fresponsible for the professional
OL,8,Fdelivery of safeguarding within the
OL,9,FChurch, nonetheless serious and
OL,10,Fsignificant failings in our central
OL,11,Fsafeguarding functions occurred partly
OL,12,Fduring my tenure as General Secretary.
OL,14,F"In light of this, I have decided it
OL,15,Fwould be best at this time for me to
OL,16,Fstep aside from my current role as
OL,17,FModerator of the General Assembly, the
OL,18,FChurch's chief public representative."
OL,20,FHe will step aside at the end of
OL,21,FNovember.
